name: piranha
description:
Piranha is a brazilian Serrasalminae fish, common in the Pantanal and Amazonia. It have one of the strongest jaws found in bony fish. Very voracious, predatory, and fast.

Piranha is also a bad word used to refer to women who doesn't fit the standart "prudish woman" paper. 

This beat was made in the 267th session of Beat Brasilis, a pioneer Brasil's beatmakers meeting, which during the pandemic is being online.

piece made to #WitchingHourOnHEN
illustration, animation & soundtrack by @numadessas at HIC ET NUNC
